<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122554b7-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1101"><num value="1101">§ 1101.</num><heading> Printing and binding for the President</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director of the Government Publishing Office shall execute such printing and binding for the President as he may order and make requisition for.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122554b8-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1261">82 Stat. 1261</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/235/dH/tI/s1301/c/1">Pub. L. 113–235, div. H, title I, § 1301(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-16">Dec. 16, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2537">128 Stat. 2537</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id122554b9-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id122554ba-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 211 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s88">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 88</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/622">28 Stat. 622</ref>).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id122554bb-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id122554bc-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section constitutes part of section 88 of act <date date="1895-01-12">Jan. 12, 1895</date>. Remainder of section is classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t44/s1713">section 1713 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id122554bd-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2014—<ref href="/us/pl/113/235">Pub. L. 113–235</ref> substituted “Director of the Government Publishing Office” for “Public Printer”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
